      "rationale": "Richardson extrapolation across three mesh levels yields GCI_fine = 4.8% for wall shear stress at the impeller trailing edge, the primary hemolysis-driving quantity. The required threshold at MRL 2 is GCI ≤ 3.0%. The shortfall is marginal (4.8% vs. 3.0%) but cannot be dismissed: wall shear stress enters the power-law hemolysis model nonlinearly (exponent ~2.4), so a 4.8% discretization error in WSS propagates to approximately 12% error in predicted hemolysis index. This exceeds the acceptable contribution from spatial discretization alone. The apparent order of convergence (p = 1.87) is slightly below theoretical (2.0), suggesting mild non-monotonic behavior in the volute region. Additional refinement to ~28M cells is required to demonstrate GCI < 3.0% before acceptance can be granted.",
