      "rationale": "CFD-predicted RHI values agree with experimental measurements within 18% at three of five operating points. However, at the two highest-flow operating points (5.0 L/min at 3500 RPM and 5.5 L/min at 3200 RPM), deviations reach 24% and 27% respectively. These two points represent the hemolysis-critical regime most relevant to the COU. The acceptance criterion requires agreement within 20% across all assessed operating points, not merely a majority. The deviations at high-flow conditions fall outside the model uncertainty envelope (95th-percentile prediction interval ±22%), confirming they are not attributable to input uncertainty alone. Gradation 1 is therefore assigned; Gradation 2 requires demonstration of agreement within the stated threshold at all COU-relevant operating points.",
