  "hasWeakener": [],
  "hasDecisionRecord": {
    "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/decision/cpb-cou1-not-accepted-2026",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/morrison-credibility-review-board",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Not accepted",
    "rationale": "The credibility assessment for COU1 (CPB hemolysis worst-case identification, MRL 2) concludes Not Accepted based on documented shortfalls in two assessed factors: (1) Discretization error achieved Gradation 1 against a required Gradation 2. The fine-mesh GCI of 4.8% for wall shear stress exceeds the 3.0% threshold. Given the nonlinear dependence of the hemolysis power-law model on WSS (exponent ~2.4), this discretization error propagates to approximately 12% error in RHI — a contribution that cannot be accepted when the total validation error budget at MRL 2 allows only 20% total deviation. (2) Output comparison achieved Gradation 1 against a required Gradation 2. Agreement within 20% is demonstrated at three of five operating points, but deviations of 24% and 27% at the two highest-flow operating points — which are the hemolysis-critical conditions most directly relevant to the COU — fall outside the model uncertainty envelope. These are not isolated low-relevance operating points; they represent the regime in which worst-case hemolysis is most likely to occur. No offset rationale is claimed. The shortfalls are considered genuine epistemic gaps requiring remediation: (a) additional mesh refinement to approximately 28M cells to achieve GCI < 3.0%, and (b) extended experimental validation at high-flow operating points, potentially including additional replicates to reduce experimental uncertainty and confirm whether the deviations reflect model-form error or experimental variability. Eleven of thirteen factors meet or exceed required levels, and the overall assessment framework is sound. Resubmission following targeted remediation of these two factors is expected to support an Accepted outcome.",
    "decidedAt": "2026-04-19T00:00:00Z"
  },
